OL,3,CWhy a council ordered almost 20 trees
OL,4,Cto be chopped down on castle grounds
OL,6,FHowever, some people feel that the
OL,7,Ftrees should not have been removed at
OL,8,Fall.
OL,10,FCouncillor Johno Lee, who represents
OL,11,FBalderton, stated: "The decision to
OL,12,Fcut down 16 trees near Newark Castle,
OL,13,Feven with full planning permission, is
OL,14,Fa clear betrayal of the residents of
OL,15,FNewark and Sherwood.
OL,17,F"The controlling group of Independents
OL,18,Fand Labour councillors were elected on
OL,19,Fa manifesto that pledged to protect
OL,20,Ftrees and green open spaces, yet now
OL,21,Fthey have gone against this promise.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
